  "prompt": "Where can I get audiobooks for free in English?",
  "response": "There are several legitimate ways to access free audiobooks in English. Here are some popular options:\n\n1. **Librivox**  \n   - **Website:** [librivox.org](https://librivox.org)  \n   - **Description:** Librivox offers free public domain audiobooks read by volunteers. You can find classic literature and other works that are no longer under copyright.\n\n2. **Project Gutenberg**  \n   - **Website:** [gutenberg.org](https://www.gutenberg.org)  \n   - **Description:** While primarily known for free ebooks, Project Gutenberg also offers a selection of audiobooks, mostly classics in the public domain.\n\n3. **Open Culture**  \n   - **Website:** [openculture.com](https://www.openculture.com/freeaudiobooks)  \n   - **Description:** Open Culture curates a list of free audiobooks available from various sources, including classics, nonfiction, and children's books.\n\n4. **Libby by OverDrive**  \n   - **App:** Available on iOS and Android  \n   - **Description:** If you have a library card, you can access thousands of audiobooks for free through the Libby app. Check with your local library to see if they partner with OverDrive.\n\n5. **Audible Free Trial**  \n   - **Website:** [audible.com](https://www.audible.com)  \n   - **Description:** Audible offers a 30-day free trial, which includes one free audiobook. You can cancel before the trial ends if you don\u2019t wish to continue.\n\n6. **Hoopla**  \n   - **App:** Available on iOS and Android  \n   - **Description:** Hoopla partners with libraries to offer free audiobooks, movies, music, and more. You\u2019ll need a library card to access its services.\n\n7. **Spotify**  \n   - **App:** Available on iOS, Android, and desktop  \n   - **Description:** Spotify has a growing selection of audiobooks, including some free titles. Search for \"audiobooks\" or check curated playlists.\n\n8. **YouTube**  \n   - **Website:** [youtube.com](https://www.youtube.com)  \n   - **Description:** Many users upload full-length audiobooks to YouTube. Search for specific titles or browse audiobook playlists.\n\n9. **BBC Sounds**  \n   - **App:** Available on iOS and Android  \n   - **Description:** BBC Sounds offers free podcasts, radio dramas, and some audiobooks. While not a traditional audiobook source, it\u2019s great for listening to stories and dramas.\n\n10. **Google Play Books**  \n    - **App:** Available on iOS and Android  \n    - **Description:** Google Play Books occasionally offers free audiobooks, especially classics. Check the \"Free\" section for available titles.\n\nAlways ensure the platforms you use are legal and respect copyright laws. Enjoy your listening!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
